    "Firstly, predicting economic conditions becomes particularly challenging due to unprecedented events, making risk assessment and forecasting difficult.",
    "Secondly, important issues such as maintaining adequate cash flow and effective working capital management pose ongoing challenges, especially when revenue streams are disrupted, and expenses remain high.",
    "Moreover, debt management becomes complicated as servicing obligations become uncertain, and accessing favorable refinancing options may be limited.",
    "Investment decision-making is hindered by challenges in asset valuation and uncertainty in evaluating long-term investments.",
    "In addition, ensuring employee financial well-being, managing payroll, and addressing insurance coverage gaps are persistent concerns."
